  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this case, the teleportation is no longer uniform. Instead, the probability of teleporting to a node is proportional to its original PageRank. Compared with part 2.3(a), the results are more concentrated on already important nodes. Nodes with high PageRank get even more visits, because they are favored both by the random walk and by teleportation. This creates a reinforcing effect, where important nodes become even more important."
   ]
  },
