   "source": [
    "2.4c"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In standard PageRank, teleportation is uniform, meaning the walker can jump to any node with equal probability. To model a situation where users only visit a set of trusted pages, we can change this by using a preference vector instead of a uniform one. This means some nodes are more likely to be chosen during teleportation. To also include self-reinforcement, we can let the teleportation depend partly on the current PageRank itself. In this way, nodes that are already important will continue to attract more attention, while still allowing user preferences to influence the results."
   ]
  }
